handleTextContent

protected ByteBuffer handleTextContent()
                                throws IOException
Description copied from class: AbstractRetrievalPostProcessor
Handles Text content. If the content type is text/xml, AbstractRetrievalPostProcessor.handleXMLContent() is called. If the content type is text/html, AbstractRetrievalPostProcessor.handleHTMLContent() is called. For all other sub-types the content is logged as a message with level Level.SEVERE.

Overrides:
handleTextContent in class AbstractRetrievalPostProcessor
Returns:
a buffer containing the retrieved text.
Throws:
